> To me, `__file__` pointing at the .so provides useful diagnostic information about what has actually been imported and we shouldn't lose that. If we want to provide information about the original source it shouldn't be at the expense of being accurate about the imported file

@da-woods 
In my point of will, unlink PyO3 or other ffi stuff, Cython is like a blackbox for write speedup static-typed code to accelerate Python. Even if the document is literally said shared library is OK, but I don't think it is the intent outcome, according to the nature and purpose of Cython.
